modules.description: This module represents image data extracted from SVG files, including dimensions and transformation matrices. It provides access to the width, height, and view transformation of an image. Use it to retrieve geometric properties and apply coordinate transformations when rendering or manipulating vector graphics.

This module implements a rasterizer for vector graphics, converting SVG paths into pixel-based images. It provides functions to create and manipulate rasterization contexts, supporting operations like rendering shapes with specified colors and transformations. Use it to generate bitmaps from vector descriptions, such as exporting SVG content to PNG or performing real-time rendering in a graphics application.

This module parses SVG content into structured geometric and styling data, converts vector graphics into drawable images, and rasterizes them into pixel buffers. It provides core types like `Image_data.t` for representing SVG-derived geometry and `Rasterizer.t` for rendering vector paths into bitmaps, enabling precise control over layout, styling, and output resolution. Use it to programmatically manipulate SVG elements, apply transformations, and generate high-quality raster outputs such as PNGs. The module integrates image data handling and rasterization to support both inspection of vector content and its conversion into display-ready formats.
